Rating: 3
I made this last night for a bunch of friends. I chose boneless chicken breasts with skin. It was quite wonderful. In the custom of this site, here are the changes I made to the recipe. I used limes, as my 99 cent store offered a giant bag this week. Other than that, I followed as directed. For those that had some trouble with too much salt, I think it's because you're supposed to only use half in the sauce and use half to season the raw chicken. If you put it all into the sauce, it would be too salty. Reading the reviews I noticed a lot of people calling the sauce/dressing a "marinade". No where in the recipe does it say to "marinade" the chicken. But I chose to use half the dressing as a marinade for about 2 hours (I was afraid the citrus would turn the poultry mushy if I went any longer). Then I grilled and drizzled the pieces with the remaining sauce. Very wonderful.

