This is a great recipe, especially for those three-legged chickens. All fowl humor aside, the idea of using the dressing on the cooked chicken, rather than as a marinade before cooking, is brilliant! I cut the recipe down to feed four, using one quite ordinary two-legged chicken, cut up. I simplified it a bit too by searing legs and breasts at the same time, cooking both over the indirect heat together, and taking the breasts off about five minutes earlier than the legs.

